  {"message":
   "SSExactMajority/Defs/ExactMajority.lean:2:18: * '. All rights reserved.':\n'Copyright (c) YYYY' should be followed by a space\n\n\nNote: This linter can be disabled with `set_option linter.style.header false`",
   "level": "warning"},
  {"message":
   "SSExactMajority/Defs/ExactMajority.lean:4:0: * '\n# Self-Stabilizing Exact Majority — Problem Definition\n\nDefinition 1 from Kanaya et al. (2025):\nA protocol P = (Q, X, Y, δ, π_out) is a self-stabilizing exact majority protocol\nif X = {A, B}, Y = {A, B, T}, and for any initial configuration C₀:\n  1. For any safe C_safe reachable from C₀: ∀ v, π_out(C_safe(v)) = majority opinion\n  2. Any execution from C₀ reaches safe configurations with probability 1.\n\nThe exact majority opinion is:\n  - A  if |V_a| > |V_b|\n  - B  if |V_a| < |V_b|\n  - T  if |V_a| = |V_b|':\nIf an authors line spans multiple lines, each line but the last must end with a trailing comma\n\n\nNote: This linter can be disabled with `set_option linter.style.header false`",
   "level": "warning"},
  {"message":
   "SSExactMajority/Defs/ExactMajority.lean:4:0: * '\n# Self-S':\nThe authors line should begin with 'Authors: '\n\n\nNote: This linter can be disabled with `set_option linter.style.header false`",
   "level": "warning"},
  {"message":
   "SSExactMajority/Defs/ExactMajority.lean:10:0: * '  ':\nDouble spaces are not allowed.\n\n\nNote: This linter can be disabled with `set_option linter.style.header false`",
